news.title: Spanish hotel chain Melia buys properties for its workers as rents surge
news.para: "Due to the boom in short-term rentals for tourists, finding an apartment for the season has become an Odyssey," Escarrer said, adding that paying employees well is no longer enough to retain talent.

news.title: Rocket Companies to buy Redfin in $1.75 billion deal
news.para: Rocket's $12.50 per share offer equates to a near 115% premium to Redfin's Friday close. Redfin's shares rose about 80%, while Rocket's fell about 8% before the bell.

news.title: Construction cost for greenfield realty projects rises 2-4% in 2024: CBRE
news.para: In 2024, cement, steel, and aluminium costs dipped by 6-8 per cent, 3-5 per cent, and 0-2 per cent, respectively, on an annualised basis, while paint costs remained stable.

news.title: NCLT approves a resolution plan for Universal Buildwell Projects
news.para: The NCLT Bench, comprising Justice Ashok Kumar Bhardwaj and Justice Subrata Kumar Dash, approved the resolution plan.

news.title: Greenfield construction costs marginally rise by 2-4% in 2024
news.para: The report thoroughly examines the evolving market landscape, analyzing factors that influence construction cost trends across major real estate asset classes.

news.title: Assam cabinet approves setting up of industrial Park including a smart township in Hajo
news.para: Cabinet approved to pursue for Majuli and Sivasagar the status of UNESCO World Heritage Site under the appropriate categories by engaging experts

news.title: Renters turn to lottery in Spain's housing crisis
news.para: Like a growing number of Spaniards, the 30-year-old auxiliary nurse and her partner, Sergio Encinas, have found themselves priced out of the real estate market as rents have soared due to insufficient supply.

news.title: Nielsen leases 2.8 lakh sq ft across Bengaluru and Mumbai
news.para: The new offices has seating capacity for 1,500 employees each. The Mumbai office, leased from Oberoi Realty Limited, spans 1.5 lakh sq. ft., while the Bengaluru office, leased from Chalet Hotels Limited, covers 1.36 lakh sq.

news.title: Stamp duty evasion recovery fine after five years, not 10 years: Karnataka HC
news.para: The court, however, said there could be an exception from the five-year limit in cases of short payment on account of fraud, collusion or wilful misstatement.

news.title: Kochi’s smart city dreams fade as deadlines loom
news.para: Originally set for March 2020, the deadline was extended due to delays, including those caused by the pandemic. However, Cochin Smart Mission Limited (CSML), the agency overseeing the projects, has struggled to ensure timely completion.

news.title: Rajasthan CM aks RIICO to develop land bank for industrial expansion
news.para: Chief Minister Bhajan Lal Sharma reiterated the state govt's commitment to achieving a $350 billion economy, ensuring the proper execution of these MoUs.

news.title: Delhi HC says survey needed of residents of slum in Okhla facing demolition
news.para: DDA has maintained the that the colony in question is not protected under the JJ Clusters List for rehabilitation published by Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board.

news.title: Fourteen fresh FIRs registered against Ansal API for fraud
news.para: The company's directors are accused of cheating buyers for failing to deliver plots and villas, despite taking substantial payments.

news.title: Japan’s Nippon Paint looks at fresh investments and acquisitions in India
news.para: Nippon Paints, which started operations in India in 2006, currently has four business divisions -- auto refinish; decorative; industrial; and automotive paints (JV with Berger).

news.title: Only 36% villages in Rajasthan complete land right records under Svamitva scheme
news.para: The scheme was inaugurated by PM Narendra Modi on National Panchayati Raj Day, April 24, 2020, with main purpose of providing officially recognised ‘record of rights' to residential property owners in inhabited (abadi) areas in villages.

news.title: Chennai: Property registration to be smarter & smoother at Adyar SRO
news.para: With 588 sub-registrar offices handling an average of 15,000 daily visitors, the govt is focusing on upgrading technology. As a model initiative, the Adyar SRO, located in Thiruvanmiyur on L B Road, Kamaraj Nagar, was selected.

news.title: Government initiates process to appoint new Odisha RERA chairperson
news.para: The housing and urban development department has issued a letter to the principal secretary of law department, asking him to attend the first meeting of the selection committee formed for appointing the chairperson and members of ORERA.

news.title: Over 400 woman applied for ownership rights in Delhi under PM-UDAY: LG office
news.para: ​In a post on X, the LG office said that out of a total 432 such applications in unauthorised colonies, filed at 10 camps held in different parts of the city on Saturday, 285 were successfully resolved, and 101 women were handed over ownership documents.

news.title: Uttarakhand: Administration removes 95 illegal encroachments in Pauri
news.para: According to officials, the administration has been taking strict action against encroachments to preserve the state's culture, tradition, and demographic balance.

news.title: Apartment sales in Nashik rises 22% to 8,583 units: Credai-Liases Foras
news.para: Liases Foras MD Pankaj Kapoor said there is a huge potential for real estate development in the city across all segments, be it housing and commercial properties.
